headline: Airlines scramble to add Caribbean flights after airspace restrictions strand tens of thousands of travelers
summary: U.S. airlines resumed flights to Puerto Rico and other Caribbean destinations early Sunday after aviation authorities lifted temporary airspace restrictions.
